/figure><p></p><p></p><p>Speaking in the session were:</p><p></p><p></p><ul><li>Daniel Weitzner, Founding Director of MIT IPRI and 3Com Founders Principal Research Scientist at MIT CSAIL</li><li>Hal Abelson, the Class of 1922 Professor of Computer Science and Engineering in the Department of Electrical Engineering and Computer Science at MIT</li></ul><p></p><p></p><p></p></div><!--end of article body--><div class="row"><div class="col-md-8 col-md-offset-2 col-sm-10 col-sm-offset-1"><div class="author-details"><div class="author-image"> <img alt='' src='https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/b92ca85daca845924d5b8d7382fcccca?s=172&#038;d=mm&#038;r=g' srcset='https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/b92ca85daca845924d5b8d7382fcccca?s=344&#038;d=mm&#038;r=g 2x' class='avatar avatar-172 photo' height='172' width='172' loading='lazy'/></div><h5><a href="https://internetpolicy.mit.edu/author/caty/" title="Posts by Caty Fairclough" rel="author">Caty Fairclough</a></h5><ul class="social-icons"></ul></div></div></div></div><div class="col-sm-3"><div class="blog-sidebar"></div></div></div><!--end of row--></div><!--end of container--></section></div><div class="clearfix"></div><div class="footer-container"><footer class="bg-primary short-2"><div class="container"><div class="row"><div class="col-sm-12"><ul id="menu-menu-2" class=""><li id="menu-item-5609" class="menu-item menu-item-type-post_type menu-item-object-page menu-item-5609"><a href="https://internetpolicy.mit.edu/privacy-policy/">Privacy Policy</a></li><li id="menu-item-5607" class="menu-item menu-item-type-custom menu-item-object-custom menu-item-5607"><a href="https://accessibility.mit.edu">Accessibility</a></li><li class=" astm-search-menu is-menu default menu-item"><form  class="is-search-form is-form-style is-form-style-3 is-form-id-0 " action="https://internetpolicy.mit.edu/" method="get" role="search" ><label for="is-search-input-0"><span class="is-screen-reader-text">Search for:</span><input  type="search" id="is-searc